{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.7",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 7 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:1",
      "text": "“Isn’t a man forced to labor on earth? Aren’t his days like the days of a hired hand?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:2",
      "text": "As a servant who earnestly desires the shadow, as a hireling who looks for his wages,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:3",
      "text": "so I am made to possess months of misery, wearisome nights are appointed to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:4",
      "text": "When I lie down, I say, ‘ When will I arise, and the night be gone?’ I toss and turn until the dawning of the day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:5",
      "text": "My flesh is clothed with worms and clods of dust. My skin closes up, and breaks out afresh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:6",
      "text": "My days are swifter than a weaver’s shuttle, and are spent without hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:7",
      "text": "Oh remember that my life is a breath. My eye will no more see good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:8",
      "text": "The eye of him who sees me will see me no more. Your eyes will be on me, but I will not be.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:9",
      "text": "As the cloud is consumed and vanishes away, so he who goes down to Sheol will come up no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:10",
      "text": "He will return no more to his house, neither will his place know him any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:11",
      "text": "“ Therefore I will not keep silent. I will speak in the anguish of my spirit. I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:12",
      "text": "Am I a sea, or a sea monster, that you put a guard over me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:13",
      "text": "When I say, ‘ My bed will comfort me. My couch will ease my complaint,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:14",
      "text": "then you scare me with dreams and terrify me through visions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:15",
      "text": "so that my soul chooses strangling, death rather than my bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:16",
      "text": "I loathe my life. I don’t want to live forever. Leave me alone, for my days are but a breath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:17",
      "text": "What is man, that you should magnify him, that you should set your mind on him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:18",
      "text": "that you should visit him every morning, and test him every moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:19",
      "text": "How long will you not look away from me, nor leave me alone until I swallow down my spittle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:20",
      "text": "If I have sinned, what do I do to you, you watcher of men? Why have you set me as a mark for you, so that I am a burden to myself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.7.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:21",
      "text": "Why do you not pardon my disobedience, and take away my iniquity? For now will I lie down in the dust. You will seek me diligently, but I will not be.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
